# Auto-Save Workflow — H5

Jordan has two projects. When he says "save" or "save my work", save BOTH.
Do NOT ask permission — just run the commands.

## Mandatory for Cursor / agents (H5)

After **any** meaningful change in this repo (code, config, i18n, rules that
ship with the app), **always** run a save in the same session **before
handing work back**, unless Jordan explicitly asked for a local-only / no-push
experiment:

```bash
bash "/Users/jordanmok/Desktop/iCloud Drive/Cursor Codes/Evair-H5/scripts/save.sh" "type: short imperative summary"
```

That commits and pushes to **all remotes** (`origin` + `aliyun`). **Netlify
does not receive a separate push** — it builds when **GitHub** (`origin`)
gets the new commit on the branch Netlify watches (production **`main`**).
So “push to Netlify” = **push to `origin main`** (via `save.sh`).

Jordan wants updates live on Netlify ASAP: **always** finish the same turn with
`save.sh` after any change you intend him to preview (never hand back only a
local diff). Typical Netlify build + CDN is **~1–3 minutes** after the GitHub
webhook; open the production URL or **Netlify → Deploys** if you need the
exact “Published” time.

If **`git push origin` fails** (e.g. “fetch first” / non-fast-forward), fix it
in the same session and finish the save — do not leave the user with only a
local commit:

```bash
cd "/Users/jordanmok/Desktop/iCloud Drive/Cursor Codes/Evair-H5"
git pull --rebase origin main
git push origin main
git push aliyun main   # if rejected after rebase: git push --force-with-lease aliyun main
```

Use `--force-with-lease` on **aliyun** only when `main` was rebased onto
`origin` and Aliyun still has the pre-rebase tip (mirror drift). Never
`--force` to `origin`.

