## Save just this project (H5)

```bash
bash "/Users/jordanmok/Desktop/iCloud Drive/Cursor Codes/Evair-H5/scripts/save.sh"
# or with a custom commit message:
bash "/Users/jordanmok/Desktop/iCloud Drive/Cursor Codes/Evair-H5/scripts/save.sh" "fix: xyz"
```

`scripts/save.sh` will:
1. `git add -A && git commit -m "<msg>"` (skipped if no changes)
2. `git push <remote> <current-branch>` for EVERY remote (GitHub, plus Aliyun once configured)
3. Exit non-zero if any push fails

## When to auto-save

Save after any of these, without asking:
- Any code change lands (no matter how small) — **includes agent-made edits**
- The user says "save", "save my work", "commit", "push"
- A feature is done
- A bug fix is verified
- Before ending a session

## Deployment (Netlify)

Netlify is wired to **GitHub**. Pushing `main` to **`origin`** triggers a
deploy; there is no Netlify CLI step in normal workflow. Feature branches
only deploy if Netlify is configured for branch deploys or after merge to
`main`.

