## Local + iCloud Aliyun backups

Jordan is **Developer** (not Admin) in ZenoSIM — if Ben revokes access or deletes a repo, Aliyun is lost. Bare mirrors protect against that.

- **Local**: `~/Aliyun-Backups/` (~84 MB)
- **iCloud Drive copy** (off-site, auto-synced): `~/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/Aliyun-Backups/`
- Contains: `EvairH5.git/`, `flutter.git/`, `admin.git/`, `laravel.git/` — all bare mirrors, all branches, full history
- Refreshed automatically in 2 ways:
  - Every `save-all.sh` (includes iCloud rsync — works because Terminal has FDA, and `/usr/bin/rsync` is in FDA list)
  - **Daily auto-backup via launchd** at every login, throttled to once per calendar day, plus 9 AM daily fallback. Script: `~/Aliyun-Backups/daily-backup.sh`. Agent: `com.jordan.aliyun-backup-daily`. Log: `~/Aliyun-Backups/logs/daily.log`. State: `~/Aliyun-Backups/.last-day-run`. Catches missed days on next boot. iCloud rsync under launchd requires FDA on `/bin/bash` too (currently only `rsync` is granted) — local git mirrors still refresh, and iCloud catches up on next interactive `save-all.sh`.
- Manual refresh: `bash ~/Aliyun-Backups/refresh.sh`
- Force daily now: `FORCE=1 bash ~/Aliyun-Backups/daily-backup.sh`
- Restore: `git clone ~/Aliyun-Backups/<name>.git ~/restored-folder`

These copies live on Jordan's devices only — the China team is completely unaffected.

## Credentials

Aliyun HTTPS password lives in **macOS Keychain** (credential.helper = osxkeychain). Never hardcode a password in a git remote URL. If you see `https://user:password@...` in any `.git/config`, strip the password and re-approve via `git credential approve`.

